# Move File Conventions

## Security — CVE-D-02 (resource_address)
`resource_address` for per-user storage **must** come from `address_system::ensure_origin(ctx)`.
Never accept it as a caller-supplied parameter.

```move
// CORRECT
let resource_address = address_system::ensure_origin(ctx);
dapp_system::set_record<DappKey>(dh, dapp_key, key, value, resource_address, false, ctx);

// WRONG — allows any caller to overwrite any user's data
public fun bad(dh: &mut DappHub, resource_address: String, ...) { ... }
```

## Version Guard — Entry of Every System Function
```move
dapp_system::ensure_latest_version<DappKey>(dh, migrate::on_chain_version());
```
Call this at the top of every public system entry function to reject stale clients after upgrade.

## Ownership Transfer — Ownable2Step
Use `propose_ownership` + `accept_ownership`. Do not transfer admin in a single step.
`pending_admin = @0x0` means no pending transfer.

## Module Structure
- `systems/`  — public API, called by DApp contracts
- `core/`     — internal storage layer, not called directly by DApps
- `codegen/`  — auto-generated, never edit by hand
- `scripts/`  — deploy_hook (init) and migrate (version)
- `utils/`    — stateless helpers (bcs, math, type_info, entity_id)
- `tests/`    — unit tests, use `#[test_only]` helpers from `codegen/init_test.move`

## Error Handling
Use generated error helpers from `dubhe::errors`:
```move
use dubhe::errors::{ no_permission_error, not_latest_version_error, ... };
no_permission_error(condition_that_must_be_true);
```
To add a new error: edit `dubhe.config.ts` → run schemagen. Never add constants to `errors.move` by hand.

## Sui SDK Reference
For Sui Move APIs, find `docs/llms-index.md` inside `node_modules/@mysten/*/` and read the index.
